<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step07_ProgressReporting"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 7 - Progress Reporting">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step07ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 7: Reporting Progress from Async Operations"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">PROGRESS: Showing the user how far along an operation is.

When a long operation runs in the background, users want to see progress
(like a progress bar or "Step 3 of 10"). .NET provides IProgress&lt;T&gt; and
Progress&lt;T&gt; to safely report progress from async methods back to the UI.

- IProgress&lt;T&gt;: An interface your async method accepts as a parameter.
  Call progress.Report(value) to send an update.
- Progress&lt;T&gt;: A class you create in the UI layer that handles the updates.
  It automatically marshals callbacks to the UI thread (so you can safely
  update controls like progress bars).

T can be any type: int (percentage), string (message), or a custom class.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="Start operation with progress bar"
                    Command="{Binding StartProcessingCommand}"
                    IsEnabled="{Binding IsRunning, Converter={StaticResource InvertBoolConverter}}"/>

            <ProgressBar Height="25" Margin="0,10" 
                         Minimum="0" Maximum="100" 
                         Value="{Binding ProgressPercentage, Mode=OneWay}"/>
            
            <TextBlock FontSize="14" 
                       Foreground="#555" Margin="0,0,0,10"
                       Text="{Binding ProgressMessage}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="220"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
